    "analysis": "We have aggregated global thresholds and filtered the incident window. Metric analysis shows multiple services breached their global P95 within the window. The most significant metric deviations (finite severity ratios) are: queue-master.cpu (severity ~2.82), shipping.cpu (~2.10), orders.cpu (~1.99), and queue-master.diskio (~1.31). Logs show many services with abnormal log.row_count (both spikes and drops) including front-end, user, queue-master, catalogue, orders, payment, carts, and shipping. Traces are absent and error_logs are empty, so we must rely on metrics + log timing to localize the root cause. To localize, we need to confirm which candidate shows an early, sustained fault (consecutive anomalies) in the window and compare occurrence times and severity among top candidates (queue-master, shipping, orders, payment, front-end). At present, queue-master stands out for the largest severity ratio and diskio and CPU anomalies, but we must verify anomaly start time and fault length (consecutive anomalous samples) relative to other candidates before declaring root cause.",
    "completed": "False",
    "instruction": "For the following candidate (cmdb_id, kpi_name) pairs: (queue-master, cpu), (queue-master, diskio), (shipping, cpu), (orders, cpu), (payment, latency-90), and (front-end, log.row_count) do the following: using the already-computed global P95 for each KPI (do not recompute thresholds from filtered data), filter metric.csv or log.csv to the incident window (2024-01-20 12:40:57 to 2024-01-20 13:10:57 UTC) and for each pair return a single compact row with these columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, p95, earliest_anomaly_timestamp_in_window (the earliest timestamp in the window where value >= p95 for metrics, or value >= p95 OR value <= p5 for logs), number_of_consecutive_anomalous_points_at_earliest_run (length of the first consecutive run of anomalous points starting at that earliest anomaly), total_anomalous_points_in_window, max_value_in_window, severity_ratio = max_value_in_window/p95 (use inf when p95==0). Limit output to these 6 rows. If a candidate has no anomalous points in the window, return earliest_anomaly_timestamp_in_window as null and zeros for counts and max_value_in_window."
